# AI Cost Optimization

# Introduction

AI Cost Optimization is one of the most important responsibilities in LLMOps and AI Infrastructure Engineering.

Large Language Models (LLMs) are extremely resource-intensive because they require:
- Expensive GPUs
- Massive inference workloads
- High-speed networking
- Large storage systems
- Continuous AI serving

Without optimization:
- AI infrastructure costs can grow uncontrollably.

---

# Why AI Cost Optimization Matters

AI systems can become expensive due to:
- GPU overprovisioning
- Inefficient inference
- Excessive token usage
- Poor autoscaling
- Underutilized infrastructure

---

# Goals of AI Cost Optimization

| Goal | Description |
|---|---|
| Reduce GPU cost | Improve utilization |
| Lower token usage | Reduce API spending |
| Optimize infrastructure | Better scheduling |
| Improve efficiency | Faster inference |
| Reduce idle resources | Elastic scaling |

---

# AI Cost Architecture

```text
Users
  ↓
