# 3. Quantization

## What is Quantization?

Quantization reduces:
- Numerical precision of models

Example:

```text
FP32 → FP16 → INT8 → INT4
```

---

# Why Quantization Matters

Benefits:
- Smaller models
- Lower VRAM usage
- Faster inference
- Reduced GPU cost

---

# Quantization Workflow

```text
Full Precision Model
        ↓
Quantization
        ↓
Compressed Model
        ↓
Efficient Inference
```

---

# Quantization Types

| Type | Description |
|---|---|
| FP16 | Half precision |
| INT8 | Integer quantization |
| INT4 | Aggressive compression |

---

# Quantization Benefits

| Benefit | Impact |
|---|---|
| Lower memory | Smaller GPUs |
| Faster inference | Better throughput |
| Reduced infrastructure cost | Cheaper serving |

---

# Quantization Tradeoff

```text
Smaller Model Size
       ↓
Possible Accuracy Loss
```

---

# Quantization Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|
| bitsandbytes | Quantized inference |
| GPTQ | Model compression |
| AWQ | Weight quantization |
| GGUF | llama.cpp models |

