# 4. Model Caching

## What is Model Caching?

Caching stores:
- Previously generated responses

to avoid repeated inference.

---

# Why Caching Matters

Repeated prompts waste:
- GPU compute
- Tokens
- API costs

---

# Model Caching Workflow

```text
User Request
      ↓
Cache Check
      ↓
Cached Response?
   Yes → Return Result
   No  → Run Inference
```

---

# Types of AI Caching

| Cache Type | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Prompt cache | Store repeated prompts |
| Embedding cache | Reuse vectors |
| Response cache | Save outputs |
| KV cache | Faster token generation |

---

# Benefits of Caching

- Lower latency
- Reduced GPU usage
- Lower token cost

---

# Cache Storage Systems

| Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Redis | Fast caching |
| Memcached | Distributed cache |
| SQLite | Lightweight caching |

---

# 5. Semantic Caching

## What is Semantic Caching?

Semantic caching retrieves:
- Similar previous responses

using embeddings.

---

# Traditional Cache vs Semantic Cache

| Traditional Cache | Semantic Cache |
|---|---|
| Exact match | Meaning-based match |
| String comparison | Embedding similarity |

---

# Semantic Cache Workflow

```text
User Query
      ↓
Embedding Generation
      ↓
Similarity Search
      ↓
Cached Semantic Match
```

---

# Example

Query 1:

```text
"Explain Kubernetes"
```

Query 2:

```text
"What is Kubernetes?"
```

Semantic caching may:
- Reuse similar responses.

---

# Benefits

- Reduced inference calls
- Lower token usage
- Faster responses

---

# Semantic Cache Components

| Component | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Embedding model | Vector generation |
| Vector DB | Cache retrieval |
| Similarity engine | Match detection |

